# nl-rag distilled facts — domain: 1801-connecticut-lieutenant-gubernatorial-election
# one declarative sentence per line; load with:  neuron --db app.db import pack.facts --scope knowledge
[src:1801-connecticut-lieutenant-gubernatorial-election/1776-connecticut-gubernatorial-election] The **1776 Connecticut gubernatorial election** took place on April 11, 1776; the offices to be filled were governor and lieutenant governor.
[src:1801-connecticut-lieutenant-gubernatorial-election/1776-connecticut-gubernatorial-election] This was the only such election to take place before Connecticut approved the Declaration of Independence on October 10, 1776.
[src:1801-connecticut-lieutenant-gubernatorial-election/1776-connecticut-gubernatorial-election] Statesman Jonathan Trumbull won the election.
[src:1801-connecticut-lieutenant-gubernatorial-election/1776-connecticut-gubernatorial-election] Trumbull had been governor of the Connecticut Colony prior to the American Revolution.
[src:1801-connecticut-lieutenant-gubernatorial-election/1776-connecticut-gubernatorial-election] The candidate for Lieutenant Governor in 1776 was Matthew Griswold, who also won his election.
[src:1801-connecticut-lieutenant-gubernatorial-election/1776-connecticut-gubernatorial-election] Trumbull went on to win successive gubernatorial elections until 1784, when he was succeeded by Griswold.
[src:1801-connecticut-lieutenant-gubernatorial-election/1777-connecticut-gubernatorial-election] The **1777 Connecticut gubernatorial election** was held on April 10, 1777, in order to elect the Governor of Connecticut.
[src:1801-connecticut-lieutenant-gubernatorial-election/1777-connecticut-gubernatorial-election] Incumbent Nonpartisan Governor Jonathan Trumbull won re-election as he ran unopposed.
[src:1801-connecticut-lieutenant-gubernatorial-election/1777-connecticut-gubernatorial-election] The exact number of votes cast in this election is unknown.
[src:1801-connecticut-lieutenant-gubernatorial-election/1777-connecticut-gubernatorial-election] On election day, April 10, 1777, incumbent Nonpartisan Governor Jonathan Trumbull easily won re-election as he ran unopposed.
[src:1801-connecticut-lieutenant-gubernatorial-election/1777-connecticut-gubernatorial-election] Trumbull was sworn in for his second term on May 10, 1777.
[src:1801-connecticut-lieutenant-gubernatorial-election/1778-connecticut-gubernatorial-election] The **1778 Connecticut gubernatorial election** was held on April 9, 1778, in order to elect the Governor of Connecticut.
[src:1801-connecticut-lieutenant-gubernatorial-election/1778-connecticut-gubernatorial-election] On election day, April 9, 1778, incumbent Nonpartisan Governor Jonathan Trumbull easily won re-election as he ran unopposed.
[src:1801-connecticut-lieutenant-gubernatorial-election/1778-connecticut-gubernatorial-election] Trumbull was sworn in for his third term on May 10, 1778.
[src:1801-connecticut-lieutenant-gubernatorial-election/1779-connecticut-gubernatorial-election] The **1779 Connecticut gubernatorial election** was held on April 8, 1779, in order to elect the Governor of Connecticut.
[src:1801-connecticut-lieutenant-gubernatorial-election/1779-connecticut-gubernatorial-election] On election day, April 8, 1779, incumbent Nonpartisan Governor Jonathan Trumbull easily won re-election as he ran unopposed.
[src:1801-connecticut-lieutenant-gubernatorial-election/1779-connecticut-gubernatorial-election] Trumbull was sworn in for his fourth term on May 10, 1779.
[src:1801-connecticut-lieutenant-gubernatorial-election/1780-connecticut-gubernatorial-election] The **1780 Connecticut gubernatorial election** was held on April 13, 1780, in order to elect the Governor of Connecticut.
[src:1801-connecticut-lieutenant-gubernatorial-election/1780-connecticut-gubernatorial-election] Incumbent Nonpartisan Governor Jonathan Trumbull won a plurality of the vote in his re-election bid against other candidates.
[src:1801-connecticut-lieutenant-gubernatorial-election/1780-connecticut-gubernatorial-election] However, as no candidate received a majority of the total votes cast as was required by Connecticut law, the election was forwarded to the Connecticut legislature, who chose Trumbull as governor.
[src:1801-connecticut-lieutenant-gubernatorial-election/1780-connecticut-gubernatorial-election] On election day, April 13, 1780, incumbent Nonpartisan Governor Jonathan Trumbull won re-election after having been chosen by the Connecticut legislature.
[src:1801-connecticut-lieutenant-gubernatorial-election/1780-connecticut-gubernatorial-election] Trumbull was sworn in for his fifth term on May 10, 1780.
[src:1801-connecticut-lieutenant-gubernatorial-election/1781-connecticut-gubernatorial-election] The **1781 Connecticut gubernatorial election** was held on April 12, 1781, in order to elect the Governor of Connecticut.
[src:1801-connecticut-lieutenant-gubernatorial-election/1781-connecticut-gubernatorial-election] On election day, April 12, 1781, incumbent Nonpartisan Governor Jonathan Trumbull won re-election after having been chosen by the Connecticut legislature.
[src:1801-connecticut-lieutenant-gubernatorial-election/1781-connecticut-gubernatorial-election] Trumbull was sworn in for his sixth term on May 10, 1781.
[src:1801-connecticut-lieutenant-gubernatorial-election/1782-connecticut-gubernatorial-election] The **1782 Connecticut gubernatorial election** was held on April 11, 1782, in order to elect the Governor of Connecticut.
[src:1801-connecticut-lieutenant-gubernatorial-election/1782-connecticut-gubernatorial-election] Incumbent Nonpartisan Governor Jonathan Trumbull won a majority of the vote in his re-election bid against other candidates.
[src:1801-connecticut-lieutenant-gubernatorial-election/1782-connecticut-gubernatorial-election] On election day, April 11, 1782, incumbent Nonpartisan Governor Jonathan Trumbull won re-election against other candidates.
[src:1801-connecticut-lieutenant-gubernatorial-election/1782-connecticut-gubernatorial-election] Trumbull was sworn in for his seventh term on May 10, 1782.
[src:1801-connecticut-lieutenant-gubernatorial-election/1801-connecticut-lieutenant-gubernatorial-election] The **1801 Connecticut lieutenant gubernatorial election** was held on April 13, 1801, in order to elect the lieutenant governor of Connecticut.
[src:1801-connecticut-lieutenant-gubernatorial-election/1801-connecticut-lieutenant-gubernatorial-election] Incumbent Federalist lieutenant governor John Treadwell defeated Democratic-Republican candidate Ephraim Kirby and other candidates.
[src:1801-connecticut-lieutenant-gubernatorial-election/1801-connecticut-lieutenant-gubernatorial-election] On election day, April 13, 1801, incumbent Federalist lieutenant governor John Treadwell won re-election by a margin of 7,028 votes against his foremost opponent Democratic-Republican candidate Ephraim Kirby, thereby retaining Federalist control over the office of lieutenant governor.
[src:1801-connecticut-lieutenant-gubernatorial-election/1801-connecticut-lieutenant-gubernatorial-election] Treadwell was sworn in for his fourth term on May 14, 1801.
